ocks from star passages through the disk, and grain growth during\n\"quiescent\" times, are mentioned as possible mechanisms of creating the unusual\ngrain size distribution. (...)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Apr 2003 18:36:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 31 Jul 2003 17:33:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-09-29"}
