easured with $\\sim 1%$ accuracy. $C_l$\nscales as $(\\Omega_b h)^2 \\sigma_8^{4\\sim 6}$. Given cosmological parameters,\nACT would be able to constrain $z_{\\rm reion}$ with several percent accuracy.\nSome multi-reionization scenarios degenerate in the primary CMB temperature and\nTE measurement can be distinguished with $\\sim 10 \\sigma$ confidence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Apr 2003 18:57:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 30 Apr 2003 01:53:14 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 3 May 2003 02:11:19 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 13 May 2003 18:00:13 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 21 Oct 2003 17:39:47 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Mon, 27 Oct 2003 22:15:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
