on with observations of the Tycho SNR suggests a delayed\ndetonation as the most probable explosion mechanism. Line strengths, line\nratios, and the centroid of the Fe Kalpha line are reasonably well reproduced\nby a model of this kind.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Apr 2003 15:45:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
